1
00:00:25,950 --> 00:00:30,400
Thank you for making time to visit, Sakuraba.

2
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:31,170
Of course.

3
00:00:31,170 --> 00:00:37,180
As you can see,
my daughter has fully recovered now.

4
00:00:37,180 --> 00:00:40,150
I'm sorry for the trouble we caused you.

5
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:42,520
Your photos turned out wonderful.

6
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:45,040
To think you would collapse at the ceremony.

7
00:00:45,040 --> 00:00:47,360
And for an ulcer, no less.

8
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:50,250
Thank goodness we had a short guest list.

9
00:00:50,250 --> 00:00:53,820
My, Kazuomi looks stunning in this shot.

10
00:00:55,260 --> 00:00:58,650
Speaking of which, how are our guests faring?

11
00:00:58,650 --> 00:01:01,980
Your friends must have been shocked.

12
00:01:01,980 --> 00:01:04,670
I only hope no rumors have spread about this.

13
00:01:04,670 --> 00:01:06,430
That won't be an issue, Mother.

14
00:01:06,430 --> 00:01:08,280
My friends are trustworthy folks.

15
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:11,750
What a relief. If rumors were to spread,

16
00:01:11,750 --> 00:01:16,530
I can only imagine how awkward
the office would get for you.

17
00:01:20,790 --> 00:01:24,050
I want my daughter and son-in-law
to lead a life of happiness.

18
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:28,260
The venue was quite lovely as well.

19
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:30,480
It was.

20
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:32,930
You look beautiful here, Mom.

21
00:01:32,930 --> 00:01:34,390
Do I?

22
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:37,650
Why did you tag along?

23
00:01:37,650 --> 00:01:41,050
Because you mentioned Sayaka was discharged.

24
00:01:42,650 --> 00:01:44,370
Did you already tell her?

25
00:01:44,370 --> 00:01:45,660
About?

26
00:01:45,660 --> 00:01:47,500
Are you kidding me?

27
00:01:50,070 --> 00:01:54,930
About the poison,
and everything else we've found out.

28
00:01:57,740 --> 00:01:59,600
Did you ask about the ConCafe?

29
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:01,570
What about those dating apps?

30
00:02:01,570 --> 00:02:04,580
Of course not.

31
00:02:04,580 --> 00:02:09,180
Sayaka would never. I won't believe it.

32
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:19,340
What are you two whispering about?

33
00:02:21,380 --> 00:02:25,470
Sakuraba was expressing his relief
to see Sayaka well again.

34
00:02:25,470 --> 00:02:26,370
Right.

35
00:02:26,370 --> 00:02:31,190
Is that so?
You're welcome to stay for cake as well.

36
00:02:31,190 --> 00:02:32,970
Thank you.

37
00:02:40,290 --> 00:02:43,100
- <i>Congrats!</i>
- <i>Congratulations!</i>

38
00:03:13,730 --> 00:03:16,810
I heard you took
their first-look photos as well?

39
00:03:16,810 --> 00:03:17,700
That's right.

40
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:20,840
They're lucky to have found
a photographer like you.

41
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:24,310
He was a pro at work. It was amazing.

42
00:03:24,310 --> 00:03:25,650
Yeah.

43
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:32,700
It's often a struggle
to capture natural expressions.

44
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:40,200
<i>But watching them from my camera,
I could see they were in their own world.</i>

45
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:43,770
<i>Sayaka didn't seem too nervous, either.</i>

46
00:03:43,770 --> 00:03:45,070
<i>Yeah.</i>

47
00:03:45,070 --> 00:03:49,120
<i>I do enjoy taking first-look photos.</i>

48
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:52,250
<i>It lets me capture couples at their happiest.</i>

49
00:03:52,250 --> 00:03:55,050
<i>All your shots turned out great.</i>

50
00:03:55,050 --> 00:03:57,330
I owe that all to my subjects.

51
00:03:57,330 --> 00:04:00,080
Don't sell yourself short.

52
00:04:01,740 --> 00:04:07,140
How else could you capture two strangers
having such a natural moment together?

53
00:04:07,140 --> 00:04:11,910
Cameras help me see the truth in people,
that's all.

54
00:04:11,910 --> 00:04:15,810
What, is that a superpower of yours?

55
00:04:15,810 --> 00:04:17,870
No, no.

56
00:04:17,870 --> 00:04:21,340
It's just a side effect
that comes with the profession.

57
00:04:21,340 --> 00:04:23,980
You're an amazing guy.

58
00:04:24,820 --> 00:04:26,540
Sayaka?

59
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:33,250
Sayaka? Are you feeling ill?

60
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:36,010
Sorry, it's just another dizzy spell.

61
00:04:36,010 --> 00:04:37,660
It's nothing serious.

62
00:04:37,660 --> 00:04:40,260
You should lie down for a bit.

63
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:41,690
- Okay.
- Let's go.

64
00:04:52,630 --> 00:04:56,050
I apologize for the scene, Sakuraba.

65
00:04:56,050 --> 00:05:00,510
You're free to stay and finish that slice.

66
00:05:00,510 --> 00:05:02,440
Right, thank you.

67
00:05:23,470 --> 00:05:27,260
<i>The poisoned bride is now in the company</i>

68
00:05:27,260 --> 00:05:32,030
<i>of two prime suspects.</i>

69
00:05:38,650 --> 00:05:41,860
I can't believe this ceremony's on a weekday.

70
00:05:41,860 --> 00:05:42,790
Yeah, seriously.

71
00:05:42,790 --> 00:05:45,890
Let's go for a smoke.
They'll get divorced anyway.

72
00:05:47,490 --> 00:05:51,350
<i>No human being is without ill will.</i>

73
00:05:51,350 --> 00:05:57,040
<i>And that includes the suspect-hunting groom.</i>

74
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:00,560
Great work out there.

75
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,500
Likewise, Ueno.

76
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:05,850
Though I know you already have our old one,

77
00:06:05,850 --> 00:06:08,440
here's our new business card, for posterity.

78
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:12,060
- Thanks, I appreciate it.
- Anytime.

79
00:06:12,060 --> 00:06:14,680
[Bridging true love and virtue]
[Honoka Ueno]

80
00:06:15,870 --> 00:06:18,450
"Virtue", huh?

81
00:06:18,450 --> 00:06:23,720
That reminds me.
The Hayashida couple visited again.

82
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:27,160
The wife seemed to be doing better.

83
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:30,030
Is that so.

84
00:06:31,140 --> 00:06:32,600
That's wonderful to hear.

85
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:36,010
I suppose the violin performance
really stressed her out.

86
00:06:36,010 --> 00:06:37,210
What?

87
00:06:37,210 --> 00:06:40,340
Mrs. Sayaka didn't seem eager to perform.

88
00:06:40,340 --> 00:06:43,620
But she said her mother insisted.

89
00:06:43,620 --> 00:06:48,120
It seems now the couple
wish to redo their ceremony.

90
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:52,400
Really? Redo it, you say.

91
00:07:05,070 --> 00:07:07,480
<i>Sayaka has always been timid.</i>

92
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:10,900
<i>It made her a magnet for trouble.</i>

93
00:07:11,870 --> 00:07:15,530
<i>She brought chaos
into my otherwise stable life.</i>

94
00:07:17,030 --> 00:07:21,280
It feels so nice out.

95
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:23,530
<i>But I have no regrets marrying her.</i>

96
00:07:31,210 --> 00:07:33,070
Pretty, aren't they?

97
00:07:40,390 --> 00:07:41,730
<i>However...</i>

98
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:06,640
I'm sorry.

99
00:08:14,540 --> 00:08:16,330
I...

100
00:08:18,060 --> 00:08:21,670
I ruined our wedding.

101
00:08:30,450 --> 00:08:33,410
No one blames you, Sayaka.

102
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:47,160
I'll be at your side, to protect you.

103
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:53,120
I keep adding to your troubles.

104
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:59,740
It's all my fault.

105
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:02,430
I made you handle the house by yourself.

106
00:09:04,030 --> 00:09:09,430
And you still visited me every day.

107
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:15,670
Jeez. Don't worry about me, alright?

108
00:09:26,870 --> 00:09:28,920
Say, Kazu.

109
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:34,150
What did you do while I was in the hospital?

110
00:09:34,150 --> 00:09:35,510
What?

111
00:09:38,060 --> 00:09:41,990
I was... well...

112
00:09:46,590 --> 00:09:50,980
I was missing every moment without you.

113
00:09:56,160 --> 00:10:00,280
I'm so grateful you're better now.

114
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,610
Shall we?

115
00:10:37,110 --> 00:10:38,860
<i>Aw, really?</i>
[Meet me downstairs]

116
00:10:38,860 --> 00:10:42,250
<i>Looks like you could use some fresh air.</i>

117
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:13,930
I'll protect you.

118
00:11:17,030 --> 00:11:19,010
No matter who you are.

119
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:29,070
Sorry, did I wake you up?

120
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:31,820
No.

121
00:11:58,380 --> 00:12:00,220
Can't sleep?

122
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:02,660
Nah.

123
00:12:04,020 --> 00:12:06,560
Here, lie down.

124
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:15,470
Good night.

125
00:12:17,530 --> 00:12:19,650
Good night.

126
00:12:50,450 --> 00:12:52,710
No matter who she is...

127
00:12:55,580 --> 00:12:57,230
Right.

128
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:30,360
[Chie: How are you? Let's meet up again.]

129
00:13:39,210 --> 00:13:43,130
<i>The first wedding that resulted in poison.</i>

130
00:13:43,940 --> 00:13:47,090
<i>Unraveling the bride's past.</i>

131
00:13:47,090 --> 00:13:48,680
Especially with her job at the ConCafe.

132
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:51,040
She had relationships
with several of her customers.

133
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:54,420
She sought out solace in dating apps as well.

134
00:13:54,420 --> 00:13:56,220
<i>And now...</i>

135
00:13:57,360 --> 00:14:00,350
A second wedding.

136
00:14:00,350 --> 00:14:07,450
<i>He now knows of his wife's "impurities",
yet pushes for a do-over. Why?</i>

137
00:14:08,460 --> 00:14:11,640
It's all the more perplexing,
given what I know of him.

138
00:14:11,640 --> 00:14:12,680
ConCafe?

139
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:15,260
That's practically like working the nightlife.

140
00:14:15,260 --> 00:14:17,110
Don't act like you have good intentions.

141
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:25,690
Did he know of his wife's past already?

142
00:14:25,690 --> 00:14:27,890
Of course not.

143
00:14:28,470 --> 00:14:30,890
Really?

144
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:37,170
What do you think he's really like?

145
00:14:40,940 --> 00:14:42,900
His anger was intense.

146
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:48,550
This all happened
before he even met the woman.

147
00:14:50,950 --> 00:14:55,220
Why do you think he's so volatile,

148
00:14:55,220 --> 00:14:56,940
Sachiko?

149
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:11,730
Guess we won't know unless we ask.

150
00:15:15,780 --> 00:15:17,860
Seriously?

151
00:15:17,860 --> 00:15:20,300
- Morning.
- Good morning.

152
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:22,100
Sorry I took such a long break.

153
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:25,230
It's no worries at all.

154
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:33,250
So, how was your time off?

155
00:15:33,250 --> 00:15:34,840
What do you mean?

156
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:38,010
You spent time with your wife, right?

157
00:15:39,250 --> 00:15:41,360
Of course I did.

158
00:15:46,410 --> 00:15:47,280
What?

159
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:50,960
Just wondering if you two
did anything special.

160
00:15:53,050 --> 00:15:54,200
Not really.

161
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:57,590
Is that so?

162
00:15:57,590 --> 00:15:59,300
Good to know.

163
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:00,710
Come here.

164
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:02,930
Quick.

165
00:16:02,930 --> 00:16:05,290
Something definitely happened.

166
00:16:07,660 --> 00:16:11,150
Hey, what's the occasion?

167
00:16:14,820 --> 00:16:16,960
I think rumors are spreading.

168
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:18,360
What?

169
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:22,350
About the wedding.

170
00:16:30,460 --> 00:16:33,290
You knew about this?

171
00:16:33,290 --> 00:16:35,260
I mean...

172
00:16:35,260 --> 00:16:37,020
Well, did you?

173
00:16:38,590 --> 00:16:41,450
Word about it spread to my department.

174
00:16:42,740 --> 00:16:44,450
Seriously?

175
00:16:44,450 --> 00:16:47,320
Some of my juniors even asked about it.

176
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:48,640
What did they want to know?

177
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:52,270
They just asked if I attended your wedding.

178
00:16:53,620 --> 00:16:59,460
And if Sayaka truly "collapsed at the altar".

179
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:05,200
You've got to be kidding me.

180
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:09,840
I still don't know who started the rumor.

181
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:21,220
But hey, don't let it get to you.

182
00:17:21,220 --> 00:17:23,430
Easy for you to say.

183
00:17:23,430 --> 00:17:27,570
I worry about people being judgemental.

184
00:17:27,570 --> 00:17:30,390
The rumor will die out in due time.

185
00:17:30,390 --> 00:17:32,220
How can you be so sure?

186
00:17:34,330 --> 00:17:38,160
"Yes, I attended the ceremony.
But no one collapsed."

187
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:41,050
"I think there's been a misunderstanding."

188
00:17:41,050 --> 00:17:44,770
That's what I've been telling everyone.

189
00:17:44,770 --> 00:17:48,010
People will forget about this soon enough.

190
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:51,070
Naoto...

191
00:17:52,740 --> 00:17:57,820
You're such a great guy. Seriously, thanks.

192
00:17:59,730 --> 00:18:04,180
Who the hell even started this rumor?

193
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:10,660
I'm blessed to have a friend like you.

194
00:18:13,850 --> 00:18:15,340
<i>I am Sayaka's best friend.</i>

195
00:18:15,340 --> 00:18:18,430
<i>Everything I've done, is for Sayaka's sake.</i>

196
00:18:19,540 --> 00:18:22,220
You owe me a meal, alright?

197
00:18:22,220 --> 00:18:25,580
Your best friend just saved your skin.

198
00:18:27,930 --> 00:18:29,410
Naoto.

199
00:18:33,310 --> 00:18:37,430
Just to get this out there,
you didn't start the rumor, right?

200
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:44,870
Kazuomi.

201
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:49,890
That's not funny, man.

202
00:18:49,890 --> 00:18:51,140
I wanted to be sure.

203
00:18:51,140 --> 00:18:53,360
You've always been like this.

204
00:18:53,360 --> 00:18:56,020
Learn some tact already.

205
00:18:56,020 --> 00:19:00,730
- I just...
- Sure, you're frustrated with what happened.

206
00:19:00,730 --> 00:19:02,400
But that's no reason to take it out on me.

207
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:03,920
I never meant to...

208
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:06,100
It's even worse if you didn't mean it.

209
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:09,110
That's the sort of thing
that eventually escalates to harassment.

210
00:19:10,330 --> 00:19:11,380
What?

211
00:19:11,380 --> 00:19:16,530
You better not be making Sayaka cry
with that sort of attitude, too.

212
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:20,780
No, I would never.

213
00:19:20,780 --> 00:19:22,040
Harassment is despicable.

214
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:24,640
A girl like her chose to marry you.

215
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:28,580
Quit acting so self-centered,
and learn to prioritize Sayaka already.

216
00:19:28,580 --> 00:19:29,630
I do prioritize Sayaka.

217
00:19:29,630 --> 00:19:32,760
I know she relies on you.

218
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:36,670
But don't think you're so above it all,
just because you're the husband.

219
00:19:36,670 --> 00:19:41,010
Sayaka's a nice girl.
Don't take advantage of her.

220
00:19:41,650 --> 00:19:42,990
I won't.

221
00:19:42,990 --> 00:19:45,760
And I know I've mentioned this before,

222
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:49,360
but inviting them to the wedding was just...

223
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:51,040
I get it already.

224
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:56,960
Before you doubt me,
watch yourself, alright?

225
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,860
Just drop it.

226
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:04,200
I'm not talking about your attitude.

227
00:20:06,710 --> 00:20:09,060
Someone's looking into you, Kazuomi.

228
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:11,840
What? Who?

229
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:15,060
That guy who was at the wedding.

230
00:20:17,690 --> 00:20:19,070
The photographer you hired.

231
00:20:19,070 --> 00:20:20,440
What?

232
00:20:28,010 --> 00:20:31,800
Might just be me overthinking it though.

233
00:20:34,850 --> 00:20:38,610
<i>It's him. He spread the rumors.</i>

234
00:20:40,070 --> 00:20:43,050
<i>He betrayed me.</i>

235
00:21:15,770 --> 00:21:18,030
Why are you snooping around?

236
00:21:20,820 --> 00:21:22,930
What are you referring to?

237
00:21:22,930 --> 00:21:25,110
You were at my office. Why?

238
00:21:28,380 --> 00:21:31,080
Did you tell my coworkers about the wedding?

239
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:31,900
Huh?

240
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:36,390
You told them about Sayaka collapsing,
didn't you?

241
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:50,840
What would I gain by doing that?

242
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:58,340
Remember, we're searching for the culprit.

243
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:02,890
I was looking into one of our suspects.

244
00:22:02,890 --> 00:22:05,060
You, as a matter of fact.

245
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,750
What?

246
00:22:13,550 --> 00:22:19,030
I was asking around about the suspect,
Kazuomi Hayashida.

247
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:25,370
You're the one who poisoned the bride,
are you not?

248
00:22:33,780 --> 00:22:35,390
You think I did it?

249
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:37,930
Why?

250
00:22:37,930 --> 00:22:43,250
Your beloved wife has a history.
She's seen other men in her life.

251
00:22:44,020 --> 00:22:46,080
Perhaps you felt particularly vengeful.

252
00:22:46,080 --> 00:22:50,200
Oh, yes. I heard the good news.

253
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:52,920
A second wedding, was it?

254
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:55,730
What's your next plot?

255
00:23:02,780 --> 00:23:05,090
Will you test your luck again?

256
00:23:11,190 --> 00:23:12,850
Shut your damn mouth.
